cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper focuses on natural language generation and specifically on generating diverse story continuations with controllable semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to achieve its goals, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the use of metrics to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed framework, which makes cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for its modeling framework, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for a collaborative writing system, which makes cs.SD (Sound) a possible sub-category as well.
